  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "Hath not the same Hezekiah taken away his high places and his {g} altars, and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, Ye shall worship before one altar, and burn incense upon it?",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Hath not the same Hezekiah taken away his high places and his ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{g}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " altars, and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, Ye shall worship before one altar, and burn incense upon it?",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(g) Thus the wicked put no difference between true religion and false, God and idols: for Hezekiah only destroyed idolatry and replaced it with true religion. Thus the papists slander the servants of God: for when they destroy idolatry, they say that they abolish religion.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
